This paper deals with natural language processing and specifically focuses on the problem of lexical choice. The use of statistical approaches and lexical co-occurrence networks suggests that this paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). Additionally, the use of machine learning techniques and evaluation on a large corpus suggests that it could also belong to the sub-categories of Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE).
